This paper deals with the problem of estimating uncertainty in neural network predictions, which is a common issue in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a new framework for estimating uncertainty in any pretrained standard neural network, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed framework on twelve real-world datasets, which suggests that it could be applied to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.NE) tasks as well. Finally, the paper uses statistical methods to justify the proposed framework, which is a topic that falls under the category of statistics (cs.ST). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.ST, in that order.
